  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Many patients who are candidates for scheduled major surgery have a pre-operative iron&#xD;
      deficiency which is poorly diagnosed. The management of per-operative iron deficiency is a&#xD;
      part of the concept of the &quot;Patient Blood Management&quot;, which is a concept recommended by&#xD;
      health regulatory agencies in many countries. The objective of this study is to obtain&#xD;
      updated data on the prevalence of iron deficiency in France in patients undergoing a&#xD;
      scheduled major surgery, applying the French recommendations (determination of ferritinemia&#xD;
      and Transferrin Saturation Factor).&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
